L15. For r̥ṣimittra, F and SI read riṣimittra. (BI reads bhoja kara bimila.) I'm pretty certain what we have here is meant to be r̥, not ri: the left-hand part looks like r, and the top looks like an i mātrā, but there is also a right-hand vertical stroke. Previous editors must have deemed this vertical to be an extension of the i mātrā of the following ṣi, but I find this unlikely, since the i-like curve on top of the alleged r comes from this vertical, not from the top of the r-like part. Altogether, the character is very similar to r̥ characters from Bhañja and Pāla records in IndoSkript, except that this one has the i-like curve on top, and does not (clearly) have the slanted connection between the r-like left-hand part and the vertical right-hand part. 
